            "answer_text": "Sam Woodman answer is wrong . C2 haplogroup is dominant among Mongols . But Turkic gene is very diverse and mostly eurasian . Turkic gene is not only mongoloid . C2 haplogroup is only dominant among Kazakh Turks . R1a haplogroup is common among Turkic people . R1a originated in northern Caucasia (or eastern Turkey) and spread to west (eastern europe) east (central asia ) south (north india,iran) Distribution of R1a (purple) and R1b (red)  Now look at national geographic genome project result . If we consider Turkic gene+Mongol gene=Central asian+east asian+asia minor . Russians 15% , Bulgarian 20% , Polish 8% , Czech 6% ,Romanian (not slavic ( 18% ) . Let\u2019s compare it to western Europeans British 0% , German 0% Also Finland Northern Siberian(uralic) gene is related to Turk-Mongols .        Now compare those European genes to Turkic people and Mongols . British and German gene is completely different , but as you can see Slavs gene is more similiar .    ",
